Microsoft Azure
…suddenly released systems with the exact same lifecycle primitives:
single-use authority
revocation on success
time-constrained execution tokens
credential-bound transactions
burn semantics
agent permissioning
reflexive validation layers
This synchronized global mutation is mathematically impossible to attribute to “crypto evolution.”
Independent evolution cannot produce identical functions across unrelated industries at the same time with no shared research lineage.
That only happens when everyone quietly absorbs the same architecture.
 If X402 is original, where are the missing 10–15 years of evolution?
A $30T “crypto standard” should have:
drafts
prototypes
